  "html": "<p>The Diablo III community APIs provide China-specific endpoints for Diablo III profiles.</p>\n<h2 id=\"diablo-iii-icons\">Diablo III Icons</h2>\n<p>Developers can fetch the images referenced by the D3 APIs by using the following URL template:</p>\n<p>   <code>http://media.blizzard.com/d3/icons/&lt;type&gt;/&lt;size&gt;/&lt;icon&gt;.png</code>.</p>\n<p>where: </p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>&lt;type&gt;</code> indicates the type of resource referenced; it can either be <strong>items</strong> or <strong>skills</strong>.</li>\n<li><code>&lt;size&gt;</code> for <em>items</em> must either be <strong>small</strong> or <strong>large</strong>.</li>\n<li><code>&lt;size&gt;</code> for <em>skills</em> must be <strong>21</strong>, <strong>42</strong>, or <strong>64</strong>. These values refer to the image size in pixels.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"host-names\">Host Names</h2>\n<p>In China, requests use the following formats: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Blizzard API request paths: <code>https://gateway.battlenet.com.cn</code> </li>\n<li>OAuth requests: <code>www.battlenet.com.cn/{API path}</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"apis\">APIs</h2>\n<p>Diablo III supports the following APIs for the China region. For information about using Blizzard APIs, see <a href=\"/documentation/guides/getting-started\">Getting Started</a>.</p>\n"
}